Mauritius First-Quarter Tourist Arrivals Rise 5.1%, Agency Says

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-04-22T08:09:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-22/mauritius-first-quarter-tourist-arrivals-rise-5-1-agency-says.html
Mauritius’s tourism arrivals for
the first quarter of this year rose 5.1 percent to 262,626
visitors compared with a year earlier, led by  France , the
 Mauritius Tourism Promotion Authority  said.  Europe accounted for 67 percent of arrivals, the Port
Louis-based agency said today in an e-mailed statement. The
number of visitors from France, the largest market, rose 8.3
percent to 92,097, the agency said.  January to March coincides with the second half of the
country’s peak tourism season. Arrivals in March declined by 2.8
percent to 83,349, according to the agency.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in  Port Louis  via Johannesburg at 
1933 or  gbell16@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor on this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 